  <description type="morphology">Plants 10–20(–40) cm, herbage villoso-tomentose, glabrate, or glabrous. Corollas
        (at least lobes) usually yellow-orange (sometimes red-tinged), 2.2–3 mm. 2n = 18,
        36.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering mid–late summer.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Open meadows, usually on well-drained soils;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–3500 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Alta., B.C., N.W.T., Nunavut, Sask., Yukon; Alaska, Calif., Colo., Idaho, Mont., Utah, Wash., Wyo.; Eurasia.</description>
